==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sac
<hw>Sac</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Sake</er>,
<er>Soc</er>.]</ety> <fld>(O.Eng. Law)</fld> <def>The privilege formerly
enjoyed by the lord of a manor, of holding courts, trying causes, and
imposing fines.</def> <rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sac</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sac
<hw>Sac</hw> <pr>(s⟦acr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>saccus</ets> a sack. See <er>Sack</er> a bag.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>See 2d <er>Sack</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A cavity, bag, or receptacle,
usually containing fluid, and either closed, or opening into another
cavity to the exterior; a sack.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sacalait</ent>⟦br⟧
